subSubSection.paragraph:
Recognition.
Mid-sized blackish species (wing length about 
5 mm
). Male (
Fig. 11
) dichoptic, frons very broad; thorax black setose, scutum densely brownish pruinescent, without distinct vittae; all mesonotal setae fine, hair-like, long, presutural dc multiserial, acr 2–4-serial, at least 10 sctl; legs robust, entirely dark brown, all tibiae only pilose ventrally, hind femur without setae on about apical 3/4 ventrally, only pale pilose, hind tibia very slender; wing faintly infuscate, halter brown; cerci prolonged anteriorly, short, extended nearly to middle of tergite 5, epandrium brown. Female legs not pennate.
